<HelpLayout title="Switching from another app" description="Import your history from FitNotes, Strong, Hevy, or Stronglifts, then pick the guide that fits how you train.">
  <h1>Switching to Badger</h1>
  <p>Coming from another tracker? Bring your history over first so your PRs and graphs start out full, then settle into how you like to train.</p>

  <h2>Your first 5 minutes</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>During first-launch onboarding, tap <strong>Import</strong>. You can also do this any time later from <strong>Settings → Import</strong>.</li>
    <li>Choose your old app: FitNotes, Strong, Hevy, or Stronglifts.</li>
    <li>Select the export file you saved from that app.</li>
    <li>Review the preview: exercises, workout days, sets, and the detected weight unit.</li>
    <li>Tap <strong>Import</strong> to bring it all in.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>What carries over</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Your exercises, your workouts, and every set within them.</li>
    <li>Weights come in their original unit, so nothing gets rounded or converted on the way in.</li>
    <li>New exercises land in an "Imported" category, so you can find and re-sort them later.</li>
    <li>If a session already exists on the same date, the imported sets merge in rather than overwriting it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The 3 things to know</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>PRs are recalculated from your imported history, so your records show up on their own without any extra step.</li>
    <li>Nothing leaves your device. The import runs locally, straight from the file you selected.</li>
    <li>You can import more than once, so a partial or second export is fine to add later.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Now pick your path</h2>
  <p>With your history in place, choose the guide that fits how you train: <a href="/guides/just-lifting">just lifting</a>, <a href="/guides/program-runner">running a program</a>, or <a href="/guides/optimizer">tracking the data</a>.</p>
</HelpLayout>
